node.text: PREMIERE! Bass anglers from around the world flock to Florida for one reason: to catch giant largemouth. But for Bass Pro Tour pro @justinlucasbass, the Sunshine State is more than just a bass-fishing playground – it’s the playing field upon which he competes for a living. In Episode 2 of “4 to 8 The Series” powered by @uafish, MLF cameras follow Lucas from the 4 a.m. darkness of Practice Day 1 through an exhausting Bass Pro Tour tournament week on the fabled waters of Central Florida.

node.text: Enter for a chance to win a Champion 100889 2500-Watt Invertor Generator from @championpowereq, the source Major League Fishing turns to for powering up the Bass Pro Tour. This ultralight model is one of the lightest in the industry and provides power on the go for camping, tailgating, RVing, hunting, and even running fishing tournaments. Two different winners will be awarded a Champion 100889 generator, so visit MajorLeaguefFishing.com to enter daily until August 15, 2021 for a chance to win.
